Since 𝓜 is trained via cross-entropy, it is a maximum likelihood estimator. Under standard asymptotic assumptions (sufficient model capacity, infinite training samples), 𝓛(x; 𝓜) converges to the likelihood of x under H₁. Therefore, the likelihood ratio test for this hypothesis is also

Λ_{\text{MI}}(x) = \frac{\mathcal{L}(x; \mathcal{M})}{\mathcal{L}(x; \mathcal{Q})}

so Λ(x) is also asymptotically optimal for membership inference.
